                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d507">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">839.51/4613: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hinkle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ciudad Trujillo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-10T09:00:00-05:00"
                            >June 10, 1938—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>33. The President on being informed of contents of Department’s telegram No. 22,
                    June 8, 3 p.m., indicated that he would have a proposal made as soon as
                    possible. He suggested that the Foreign Secretary in drawing up his proposal
                    should consult with Minister Norweb whenever possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hinkle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
